    <p class="text-center">All the annual land cover/use maps of the MapBiomas are produced from the pixel-per-pixel classification of Landsat satellite images. Every process is done with extensive machine learning algorithms through the Google Earth Engine platform that offers immense processing power in the cloud. In order to facilitate the parameterization of the algorithms and the organization of all the processing steps, the IBGE's  1 x 1.5o (lat / long) tiles are used. There are 556 tiles covering Brazil.</p>
